# Cursor AI Rules

# Code Style

- Follow TypeScript best practices
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use proper TypeScript types and interfaces
- Follow React Native best practices

# File Organization

- Keep components in the components directory
- Keep screens in the app directory
- Keep styles in the theme directory
- Keep utilities in the utils directory

# Naming Conventions

- Use PascalCase for component names
- Use camelCase for functions and variables
- Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants
- Use kebab-case for file names

# Documentation

- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions
- Document component props with TypeScript interfaces
- Add comments for complex logic
- Keep comments up to date with code changes
- Write all comments in lowercase
- Keep comments concise and to the point

# Testing

- Write unit tests for complex logic
- Test components in isolation
- Use proper test descriptions
- Follow testing best practices

# Security

- Never expose API keys or sensitive data
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Follow security best practices
- Validate user input

# Performance

- Optimize render performance
- Use proper memoization
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Follow React Native performance best practices

# Accessibility

- Add proper accessibility labels
- Support screen readers
- Follow WCAG guidelines
- Test with accessibility tools
